chara.textHome: I'm Shizuku Hozumi.

My parents run a cafe...which sounds cool,
but it's one of those really old ones
that don't serve anything fancy.
You can still come over if you like.
I wait on customers, so...

Um, this ended up more of an introduction
for our cafe than me.

Sorry, I really don't have
a lot of hobbies or anything...

No matter the path you choose, feelings
for those close to you will never change.

Knowing that, I can almost imagine
who I will become.

Yes, I feel the power...
Far-off places now seem within reach.

I wonder if everyone can find the place
they belong in the heart of
their special someone...

Someday, it would be nice if someone finds
the place they belong in my own heart.

I suppose you might call that thinking
a dream for the future, too.

Am I allowed to think that...
I belong right here?

I'm still too uncertain to say for sure...
But, I want to be here.

Because I think that as long as
I'm beside someone dear to me,

I'll be able to put one foot
firmly in front of the other.
Welcome. Are you just having tea today?
Or would you like a snack before you go?

There aren't many customers right now,
so you can stay as long as you like.
Good morning.
...You look sleepy.
Did you stay up late last night?
We also serve some food at our restaurant.

There's spaghetti and sandwiches
on the menu...
There's still a little time before we close.
Would you like some coffee?
You like it with milk and no sugar,
right?
Yes, I remember.
Are you not going to sleep yet?
Yeah, I think I'll stay up a bit more too.
Well...It may not be a very cool place,

but it's a traditional coffee shop
and somewhere you can relax...
I like it.
Should we leave soon?
I can go whenever.
I'll wait until you're ready.

Fights can be dangerous
and that is certainly scary,

but you can't run away if you
want to achieve your dreams.
I tried making a croque madame.
Do you want to try it?

I was thinking about putting
it as a new dish on the menu.
Perhaps it's a bit too hip for our place...
Do I seem like I'm bored to you?
I actually enjoy talking to you like this...
I'm sorry I can't express that very well.
I have my parents, my friends...
I should consider myself lucky, but...
I wonder if wanting more means I'm selfish...

Milkshakes are a staple on a coffee 
shop menu, but I don't really like them...

I just can't really stomach the idea of
drinking something with raw eggs in it...
Tsuruno...
She's as honest as a child. I envy that.
I'm not making fun of her...
I really do envy that.

Sometimes you argue with close friends
precisely because they're your close friends...

That's what I think when
I see Tsuruno and Felicia...
They make a great team.

By spending a lot of time together
you form a bond.
I think that's how you become family.
I learned that from Yachiyo and the others...
Magical Girls...

We all bear the same fate. When I
think about what she said, I wonder...

Could I have talked to Yachiyo
more about it?
I wished to be taken to where Mr. R was...

Maybe if I'd wished for something else
I could have saved him...
I'm feeling just a tad nervous...
I didn't even know what I was doing...
Yeah, I'm happy too.
How does my smile look?
Do I belong here like everyone else...?
I'm Shizuku Hozumi.
Sorry if I seem curt.

I'm not very good at expressing myself.
Don't worry, it's nothing personal.

I need to get stronger...
so I can find my way to the place
I'm searching for.

I can travel anywhere without fear.
Because I have somewhere
to come home to...
It's as though the fog is gone...
Even the scenery looks different somehow.

I must find my future self
as quickly as possible.

For every moment I spend adrift,
my future self remains lost.

I wonder if, even without being
passionate about any one thing,

my feelings for someone dear can also
serve as a road sign to the future.
